          "type": "output_text",
          "text": "There's a lot of buzz on X about Anthropic's Claude models right now, especially rumors of an imminent **Claude Sonnet 5** release (potentially today or this week, with model ID hints like `claude-sonnet-5-20260203`).[[1]](https://x.com/i/status/2018245251572396304)[[2]](https://x.com/i/status/2018981033295716510) Users are hyped about speculated specs: 1M context window (vs. Opus's 200K), outperforming Opus 4.5 on benchmarks, 2x cheaper, and faster.[[3]](https://x.com/i/status/2018588056152936784)\n\n### Key Highlights from Top Posts:\n- **Coding & Dev Tools**: Claude Code (often paired with Opus 4.5 or Sonnet 4.5) is praised for building MVPs, tweaks via Antigravity, and Xcode integrations—but some report issues like inconsistent model usage (e.g., promised Opus but got Sonnet).[[4]](https://x.com/i/status/2017873446538297439)[[5]](https://x.com/i/status/2018856222959530371)[[6]](https://x.com/i/status/2017571096833474874)[[7]](https://x.com/i/status/2018726121982849449)\n- **Opus 4.5 Praise**: Still seen as the \"gold standard\" for deep reasoning, heavy coding, and analysis in early 2026.[[8]](https://x.com/i/status/2017523175089926211)\n- **Waiting Game**: Multiple devs are \"waiting\" for Sonnet 5, predicting IT market disruption.[[9]](https://x.com/i/status/2018852037203792237)[[10]](https://x.com/i/status/2018809089506386360)\n\nOverall sentiment is excited but speculative—no official confirmation from Anthropic yet. If you're building with Claude, Sonnet 4.5 seems solid for everyday tasks while Opus handles the heavy lifting.[[8]](https://x.com/i/status/2017523175089926211) Let me know if you want deeper dives into specific posts, threads, or videos!",
